<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>QUOTE OF THE DAY</b></font><br>

<font size="2">"A horrible fire burst open the door like the Devil himself
was coming through." <br>
<a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/international/middleeast/21EGYP.html?todaysheadlines">YASSER FUAD,</a>on Egypt's railroad disaster.


<hr size="1">



<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>NATIONAL</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/education/21SCHO.html?todaysheadlines">Cleveland School Vouchers Weighed by Supreme Court</a></b><br>
The Supreme Court on Wednesday heard arguments on whether the government should grant school vouchers for education at religious schools.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/national/21BODI.html?todaysheadlines">Dazed by Crematory Scandal, Undertakers' Trust Is Shaken</a></b><br>
The alleged negligence of a couple entrusted with the cremation of bodies could be costly for their customers, who all own funeral homes.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/national/21GUNS.html?todaysheadlines">U.S. Gun Sales Are Hampered as Forms Lag Behind Rules</a></b><br>
Gun sales across the country were hampered this week after federal authorities failed to provide gun dealers with new background check forms.
<P>
</font>













<p>
