<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>INTERNATIONAL</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/international/asia/21STRA.html?todaysheadlines">C.I.A. Warns That Afghan Factions May Bring Chaos</a></b><br>
The Central Intelligence Agency has warned in a report that Afghanistan could fall into violent chaos if tensions between rival warlords are not restrained.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/international/middleeast/21MIDE.html?todaysheadlines">Israel Steps Up Counterstrikes; 22 Arabs Slain</a></b><br>
Israeli forces killed at least 22 Palestinian security officers and militants on Wednesday in retaliation for an ambush in which six Israeli soldiers were slain.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/international/asia/21PREX.html?todaysheadlines">Bush Says U.S. and China Want to See Koreas Unified</a></b><br>
President Bush and President Jiang Zemin of China said on Thursday that they would work together on reunification of North and South Korea.
<P>
</font>













<p>
