<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>BUSINESS</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/technology/21GLOB.html?todaysheadlines">Deal's Loose Ends Are Tied to Global Crossing</a></b><br>
Two top executives at Global Crossing were arranging a side deal with a firm that has ties to an Asian alliance now trying to buy the company out of bankruptcy.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/business/media/21NETW.html?todaysheadlines">Ownership Ruling Is Latest Boon to Industry Once Seen as Doomed</a></b><br>
A federal appeals court decision that could end limits on the ownership of TV stations is only the latest positive turn for an industry that has had a streak of good fortune.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/business/21INSU.html?todaysheadlines">Two Insurers Seek to Void Enron Policies</a></b><br>
Two big insurers are balking at honoring policies they wrote covering Enron's directors and officers against the cost of lawsuits, recent court filings show.
<P>
</font>













<p>
<a href="http://www.nytimes.com/pages/business/index.html?todaysheadline">MORE BUSINESS NEWS</a>
