<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>TECHNOLOGY</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/technology/circuits/21TIPS.html?todaysheadlines">Whistle-Blower Sites Mine Clues Amid Mountains of Suspicion</a></b><br>
There are now many Web sites that invite anonymous visitors to tip off authorities about potential wrongdoing. But how much quality information can be gained this way?
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/technology/21GLOB.html?todaysheadlines">Deal's Loose Ends Are Tied to Global Crossing</a></b><br>
Two top executives at Global Crossing were arranging a side deal with a firm that has ties to an Asian alliance now trying to buy the company out of bankruptcy.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/technology/circuits/21TOYS.html?todaysheadlines">Toyland Is Tough, Even for Robots</a></b><br>
For toy creator Mark Tilden, simpler is better when it comes to robotic toys. But navigating the road from lab to market, he learned, was anything but simple.
<P>
</font>













