<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>POLITICS</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/international/asia/21PREX.html?todaysheadlines">Bush Says U.S. and China Want to See Koreas Unified</a></b><br>
President Bush and President Jiang Zemin of China said on Thursday that they would work together on reunification of North and South Korea.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/politics/21DIST.html?todaysheadlines">Fight Over Political Map Centers on Race</a></b><br>
The Justice Department is attempting to block a redistricting plan for Mississippi Congressional seats supported by blacks and Democrats.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/politics/21PEAC.html?todaysheadlines">Interest in Peace Corps Rises After Bush Plea</a></b><br>
Application requests for the Peace Corps have increased 39 percent since President Bush's promise to more than double the Corps numbers.
<P>
</font>













