<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>SPORTS</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/olympics/21SKEL.html?todaysheadlines">A Family's 3rd Olympian Wins Gold</a></b><br>
With his grandfather's funeral card tucked inside his helmet, American Jim Shea won the gold medal in skeleton. American Tristan Gale won the women's gold.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/sports/basketball/21KNIC.html?todaysheadlines">Knicks Easy Mark for Even the Bulls</a></b><br>
Allan Houston scored 34 points and Latrell Sprewell added 30, but the Knicks dropped to 20-32 after losing to the Bulls on Wednesday night at the United Center.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/sports/baseball/21METS.html?todaysheadlines">Alomar Will Give the Mets a Player Who Does It All</a></b><br>
Manager Bobby Valentine hopes his other players will benefit from watching and talking to Robbie Alomar.
<P>
</font>













<p>
