<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>ARTS</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/books/21ALGE.html?todaysheadlines">A Former Algerian Army Officer Loses His Pseudonym</a></b><br>
In Algeria he was a soldier who had to camouflage the fact he was a writer. Now that he has moved to the South of France, Mohamed Moulessehoul has revealed his identity.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/arts/design/21ELEP.html?todaysheadlines">A Grateful Artist Who Wants to Repay His Elephant Helpers</a></b><br>
Three Asian elephants named Mya, Layang Layang and Dilberta have spent that last decade replenishing the supply of dung that Chris Ofili uses in nearly all his paintings.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/arts/design/21ARTS.html?todaysheadlines">From Ordinary Faces, Extraordinary Ads</a></b><br>
"The Genius and Wit of Howard Zieff" highlights the work of perhaps the most significant advertising photographer in New York in the 1960's.
<P>
</font>













<p>
