<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>NY REGION</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/nyregion/21DEBT.html?todaysheadlines">Mountain of 90's Debt Looms as City and State Feel Pinch</a></b><br>
New York City and New York State are  the largest debtors in the nation, with $42 billion and $38 billion in loans outstanding, respectively.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/nyregion/21FUND.html?todaysheadlines">Officers' Widows Oppose Control of Twin Towers Fund by Giuliani</a></b><br>
The widows of 15 police officers killed at the World Trade Center want to stop the transferring of control of the Twin Towers Fund to a private charity.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/21/nyregion/21CANT.html?todaysheadlines">Cantor at Temple Emanu-El Is Accused of Molesting Nephew</a></b><br>
The cantor of Temple Emanu-El was arrested in a case that prosecutors say lays out a pattern of sexual abuse within the family.
<P>
</font>













